## 🐛 Bug Report

`WorksheetReader.name` is set by the library, but it is not defined in the TypeScript types.

Lib version: 4.4.0

## Steps To Reproduce

<!-- The exact steps required to reproduce the issue, ideally with a code example -->

```typescript
for await (const worksheetReader of workbookReader) {
  console.log(worksheetReader.name);
}
```

TypeScript will highlight `worksheetReader.name` as an error without casting.

## The expected behaviour:

TypeScript should not complain about accessing the `name` property.

## Possible solution (optional, but very helpful):

```diff
class WorksheetReader {
    constructor(options: WorksheetReaderOptions);
+     readonly name: string;
    read(): Promise<void>;
    [Symbol.asyncIterator](): AsyncGenerator<Row>;
    parse(): AsyncIterator<Array<any>>;
    dimensions(): number;
    columns(): number;
    getColumn(c: number): Column;
}
```
